This paper focuses on using deep learning methods, specifically recurrent neural networks, for named entity recognition in the health domain. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of specialized word embeddings, which involves training embeddings on health domain datasets such as MIMIC-III. This could potentially fall under sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models on three different datasets, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
